external_knowledge:
- "guiding lights" refers to principal investigators in the context of leading research or project endeavors; 
- "treasure chests" metaphorically refers to programs that contain resources and projects; 
- "gold" symbolizes the budget or financial resources allocated to each program.

- In this context, a "captain" refers to a principal investigator (pi).;
- "Vast fleets" metaphorically represent a high number of projects.;
- "Navigated more than five ships" means having managed more than five projects.;
- "Tumultuous waters of research" metaphorically represents the challenges and complexities involved in managing research projects.

sql:
SELECT projects.title, principal_investigators.pi_name, principal_investigators.email
FROM projects
INNER JOIN principal_investigators ON projects.pi_id = principal_investigators.pi_id;

SELECT p.title, c.role
FROM projects p
JOIN collaborations c ON p.project_id = c.project_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM programs 
WHERE status = 'Active' AND budget > 10000;

SELECT * FROM projects
ORDER BY start_date ASC
LIMIT 1;

external_knowledge:
- "programs" refers to the academic or research programs;
- "projects" means the individual research or academic tasks within the programs;
- "leaders" in this context are the principal investigators in charge of the projects.
